# init()

**Initializer**

Creates a new object.

## Declaration

```swift
init()
```

## Discussion

When you create a new [doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView], it automatically creates an [doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/RenderCallbacks-swift.struct] object and assigns it to the [doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/renderCallbacks-swift.property] property. Your code won’t usually need to create [doc://com.apple.RealityKit/documentation/RealityKit/ARView/RenderCallbacks-swift.struct] objects.
